    dc:creator "Klautau, Michelle; Imešek, Mirna; Azevedo, Fernanda; Pleše, Bruna; Nikolić, Vedran; Ćetković, Helena" ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Adriatic calcarean sponges (Porifera, Calcarea), with the description of six new species and a richness analysis" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832989>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832991>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832999>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832993>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832995>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833001> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832989>
    dc:description "Fig. 14. Sycon ancora sp. nov., holotype (PMR 17809 = UFRJPOR 8345). A. Specimen in ethanol. B. Cross section. C. Detail of the distal cone. D. Tubar and subatrial skeletons. E. Atrial skeleton (white" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832989/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832991>
    dc:description "Fig. 15. Sycon ancora sp. nov., holotype (PMR 17809 = UFRJPOR 8345). A. Cortical diactine. B–C. Anchor-like tetractines. D–E. Triactines of the cones. F–H. Tubar triactines. I. Subatrial triactine. J. Atrial triactine. K. Atrial tetractine. Scale bar D–K = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832991/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832999>
    dc:description "Fig. 19. Maximum likelihood tree based on partial 28S rDNA sequences of Calcaronea. Bayesian posterior probabilities (PP) and bootstrap values (BS) are given near the branches (PP/BS; when>0.50). Adriatic specimens are written in bold. Adriatic specimens obtained in this study are marked with an asterisk. The detached tree shows the only difference in the topology of the ML and Bayesian analyses." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832999/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832993>
    dc:description "Fig. 16. Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on ITS1-5.8S-ITS2 rDNA sequences of Calcinea. Bayesian posterior probabilities (PP) and bootstrap values (BS) are given near the branches (PP/BS; when>0.50). Adriatic specimens are written in bold; *Adriatic specimens obtained during this study; **Mediterranean specimens of Borojevia cerebrum; ***Brazilian specimens of Clathrina conifera." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832993/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832995>
    dc:description "Fig. 17. Maximum likelihood tree (ML) based on partial 28S rDNA sequences of Calcinea. Bayesian posterior probabilities (PP) and bootstrap values (BS) are given near the branches (PP/BS; when>0.50). Adriatic species are written in bold.Adriatic specimens obtained in this study are marked with an asterisk." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832995/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833001>
    dc:description "Fig. 20. Species richness in the Adriatic Sea divided by sectors.: 1–9 species;: 10–17 species;: 18–26 species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3833001/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

